#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:194
msgid ""
"Jacques is certain they are very deep. Radiant heat from a distant lava "
"stream caresses his face and hands, exotic plants surround, while pools of "
"water drip and shimmer in the background. There is no doubt these are "
"strange lands... strange people..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:199
msgid ""
"Jacques's ragged group comes to a halting stop lost in these unfamiliar "
"surroundings. In the middle distance are three great thrones, two occupied. "
"A heavily armed and armored man puts himself in their path, bemused."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:204
msgid "An odd lot we have got again, wouldn't you say Your Highness?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=King Bombasan
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:208
msgid "As long as they do their job, Popper, as long as they do their job."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:212
msgid "Of course, Your Highness. Allow me to brief our new servants."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:216
msgid ""
"Welcome to the Wild Plains! As everything in life, you are here to serve a "
"purpose. Your purpose is to secure the safety and productivity of our work "
"force from the depredations of beasts that roam the plains."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:220
msgid ""
"You need not ask why this task falls to you. You need only know my "
"expectations of your performance. The two most common beasts you-"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:253
msgid "Ahh, a picture is worth a thousand words, wouldn't you say?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:257
msgid ""
"Argh! Ruphulus, I don't think that was the best idea. You lot! I suppose "
"this will be your first little test. Help rid us of these creatures, quick! "
"And try not to get yourselves killed!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=King Bombasan
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:272
msgid "A shame indeed, he seemed to show promise, this young lad."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:286
msgid "I am sorely wounded! Quick, Ruphulus, get me out of here!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:299
msgid "Hahahaha! Having fun yet?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:320
msgid "Die, beast!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:327
msgid "Two down, two more to go!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:334
msgid "Only one more left!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:341
msgid "We did it!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:345
msgid "Hahahaha, well done, kids."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=King Bombasan
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:349
msgid ""
"Ruphulus, your sense of humor is quite... astounding. Please do not bring "
"these creatures into our halls again."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:353
msgid "But of course, Your Majesty. Your wish is my command, without a doubt."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:358
msgid ""
"(<i>To the guards</i>) OK, enough <i>fun</i> for one day, I reckon. Take the "
"recruits to quarters. Allow them food and rest. (<i>To Jacques's little "
"group</i>) Tomorrow morning your work will commence."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:362
msgid ""
"<big>You, man! Clean up this mess! What do I want? The floors polished "
"clean! When do I want it? Now!</big>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/02_Captivity.cfg:379
msgid ""
"Too slow in his task, Jacques is declared both incompetent and subversive. "
"Hence, he is denied hunter duties and sent to the mines, left to rot there "
"until the end of his days..."
msgstr ""

